{{Italic title}}
The '''''Annales de la Faculté des Sciences de Toulouse''''' is a [[peer-reviewed]] [[scientific journal]] covering all fields of [[mathematics]]. Articles are written in English or French. It is published by the [[Institut de Mathématiques de Toulouse]] and edited with the help of the Centre de diffusion de revues académiques mathématiques. The [[editor-in-chief]] is Vincent Guedj ([[Université Paul Sabatier]]). The journal is abstracted and indexed in ''[[Zentralblatt MATH]]''.<ref name=MATH>{{cite web |url=http://www.zentralblatt-math.org/serials/ |title=Serials Database |publisher=[[Springer Science+Business Media]] |work=[[Zentralblatt MATH]] |accessdate=2015-08-07}}</ref>

== History ==
The journal was established in 1887 by [[Marie Henri Andoyer]], [[Benjamin Baillaud]], G. Berson, T. Chauvin, E. Cosserat, A. Destrem, C. Fabre, A. Legoux, [[Paul Sabatier (chemist)|Paul Sabatier]], and [[Thomas Joannes Stieltjes]]. Originally, the journal was [[multidisciplinary]]; the present version corresponds to the original "Mathematics" section.

