[[File:Chateau Vial in Togo.jpeg|thumb]]
'''Château Vial''' is a [[chateau]] in the hills to the north of [[Kpalimé]], in the [[Kloto Prefecture]] of [[Togo]].

It was built by the French in the early 1940s and consists of a main building and a tower. The building is owned by the Togolese government and is used for cabinet meetings. In the past presidents such as [[Félix Houphouët-Boigny]] and [[Abdou Diouf]] have stayed at the chateau. It underwent renovation in 1979.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.republicoftogo.com/Toutes-les-rubriques/Culture/Chef-d-oeuvre-en-peril|title=Chef d'ouvre en péril|publisher=Republicoftogo.com|accessdate=2 January 2015|date=18 April 2008|language=French}}</ref>

