[[File:Ålesund komm.svg|thumb]]
The '''[[coat of arms]] of [[Ålesund]]''' was approved by Royal Resolution on April 1, 1898. It was created by the artist Andreas Bloch (1860–1917). The motif, a fishing boat described in 1762 on [[Sunnmøre]], alludes to the city's history and commerce.

