The '''Confederation of African Athletics (CAA)''' (also known by its French name Confédération Africaine d'Athlétisme) is the continental association for the sport of [[athletics (sport)|athletics]] in [[Africa]]. It is headquartered in [[Dakar]], [[Senegal]]. It organises the [[African Championships in Athletics]] and other continental competitions. The body's president is [[Hamad Kalkaba Malboum]] of Cameroon.

