{{Expand Luxembourgish|date=June 2010|D'Lëtzebuerger Land}} {{Infobox newspaper | name = d'Lëtzebuerger Land | logo = | image = | caption = | type = [[Weekly newspaper]] | format = | owners = | founder = | publisher = | editor = | chiefeditor = | assoceditor = | maneditor = | newseditor = | managingeditordesign = | campuseditor = | campuschief = | opeditor = | sportseditor = | photoeditor = | staff = | foundation = 1 January 1954 | political = | language = [[German language|German]], [[French language|French]] and [[Luxembourgish language|Luxembourgish]]. | ceased publication = | headquarters = | circulation = 7,000 (2004) | sister newspapers = | ISSN = | oclc = | website = [http://www.land.lu www.land.lu] }} '''''d'Lëtzebuerger Land''''' is a weekly newspaper published in [[Luxembourg]]. It is in [[German language|German]], [[French language|French]] and [[Luxembourgish language|Luxembourgish]].
==History and profile== ''d'Lëtzebuerger Land'' was established in 1954.<ref>{{cite web|title=Media|url=http://www.luxembourg.public.lu/catalogue/medias/ap-medias/AP-Medias-2013-EN.pdf|publisher=Grand Duchy of Luxembourg|accessdate=14 November 2014}}</ref><ref name=rko>{{cite book|author=Romain Kohn|editor=Ana Karlsreiter|title=Media in Multilingual Societies. Freedom and Responsibility|date=2003|publisher=Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe|location=Vienna|url=http://www.osce.org/fom/13874?download=true|accessdate=22 January 2015|chapter=Luxembourg}}</ref> The founders were a group of financiers.<ref name=rko/>
The newspaper received €259,954 in annual [[Press subsidy in Luxembourg|state press subsidy]] in 2009.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gouvernement.lu/publications/informations_gouvernementales/rapports_activite/rapports-activite-2009/01-etat/etat.pdf |title=Ministère d'État|work=Service Information et Press|accessdate=20 November 2010}}</ref>
In 2004 the circulation of ''d'Lëtzebuerger Land'' was 7,000 copies.<ref>{{cite book|title=The Media in Europe|last1=Hirsch|first1=Mario|authorlink=Mario Hirsch|editor1-last=Kelly|editor1-first=Mary J.|editor2-last=Mazzoleni|editor2-first=Gianpietro|editor3-last=McQuail|editor3-first=Denis|year=2004 |publisher=Sage|location=London|chapter=Luxembourg|page=140|isbn=978-0-7619-4132-3|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_KRfXsBUBeAC}}</ref>
