{{Infobox mountain range <!-- *** Heading *** --> | name = Terskey Ala-Too | native_name = Тескей Ала-Тоо | other_name = <!-- *** Names **** --> | etymology = <!-- *** Image *** --> | photo = E8269-Tamchy-skyline.jpg | photo_caption = Terskey Alatau range seen from across [[Issyk Kul Lake]] | photo_size = 250 <!-- *** Country *** --> | country = [[Kyrgyzstan]] | state = | region = [[Issyk-Kul Region]] | district = <!-- *** Family *** --> | border = <!-- *** Locations *** --> | highest = Karakol Peak | elevation_m = 5216 | coordinates = {{coord|42|10|N|78|28|E|type:mountain|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | range_coordinates = | length_km = 354| length_orientation = E-W | width_km = 40 | width_orientation = N-S | area_km2 = <!-- *** Features *** --> | geology = | orogeny = | period = | biome = <!-- *** Maps *** --> | map =Kyrgyzstan | map_caption = }} The '''Terskey Alatau''' or '''Terskey Ala-Too''' ({{lang-ky|Тескей Ала-Тоо}}, {{IPA-ky|teskéj ɑlɑtoːsú|}}) is a [[mountain range]] in the [[Tian Shan]] mountains in [[Kyrgyzstan]]. It stretches south and southeast of Lake [[Issyk Kul]], from the river [[Joon Aryk]] near [[Kochkor]] in the west to the far northeastern part of Kyrgyzstan. The length of the range is 354&nbsp;km and the highest peak is [[Karakol Peak]] (5,216 m).<ref name="encyc">{{cite book|script-title=ru:Иссык-Куль.Нарын:Энциклопедия|trans-title=Encyclopedia of Issyk-Kul and Naryn Oblast|first=|last=|publisher=Chief Editorial Board of Kyrgyz Encyclopedia|language=Russian|location=Bishkek |year=1991|isbn=5-89750-009-6|pages=512}}</ref> Another high peak is [[Boris Yeltsin Peak]] (5,168 m).
==Geology==
Teskey Ala-Too is composed of [[granite]]s and [[granodiorite]]s of [[Caledonian orogeny|Caledonian]], and granites, metamorphic [[schist]]s, [[quartzite]]s, [[sandstone]]s, and [[limestone]]s of [[Paleozoic]]. [[File:Kyrgyzstan Canyons Dzhety Oguz 001.jpg|thumb|none|Broken Heart Rock, in the Jety-Oguz Valley in the Terskey Ala-Too]] ==References== {{reflist}} ==External links== *{{commons category-inline|Terskey Alatau}}
